==English==
===Etymology===
From the {{ang}} ''[[geomor]]'', ("to [[camplain]]"), from the [[w:German language|German]] ''[[jammer]]'', ("lamentation").

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-yammer.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æmə(r)|-æmə(r)]]

===Intransitive Verb===
{{en-verb}}
# To [[complain]] [[peevishly]].
# To talk [[loudly]]; to make an [[outcry]].

===Synonyms===
*[[complain]]
*[[whine]]
*[[grumble]]

===Transitive Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# to [[utter]] [[clamorously]]

===Synonyms===
*[[prattle]]
*[[babble]]
*[[yak]]

===Noun===
'''yammer'''

# The act or noise of [[yammering]].
# A loud [[noise]].
# One who [[yammers]].

